SIMPLE: groggy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Groggy
<hw>Grog"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Overcome
with grog; tipsy; unsteady on the legs.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Weakened in a fight so as to stagger; -- said of
pugilists.</def> <mark>[Cant or Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Man.)</fld> <def>Moving in a hobbling manner, owing
to tender feet; -- said of a horse.</def> <rj><au>Youatt.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Grogran</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Grogram</ent>⟦br⟧
